Job Description:
Job Responsibilities:
Performs soil collection and decontamination activities (manually and/or mechanically) on surgical instruments, utensils and equipment;
Inspects, assembles and packs instrument sets, procedure sets, utensil sets and all other reusable supplies according to the hospitals requirements;
Operates sterilizers to sterilize instrument sets, procedure sets, utensil sets and all other reusable supplies and monitor its recordings;
Performs quality controls, i.e. load check, soil test, ATP, cultures and its readings when required;
Storage of sterile items after sterilisation;
Supervises distribution of sterile supplies used in the hospital;
Assists supervisor in inventory and other areas when needed;
Acts as first point of contact for user departments regarding problems with instruments or supplies;
Prepares and issues emergency supplies on demand;
Prepares reports on hazards occurring in area of responsibilities and control issues of sterile inventory; and
Assists in orientation and continuing training of other new personnel.
Job Requirments:
Relevant Diploma with a minimum 4 years experience;
GCE A/ O/ N or equivalent with a minimum 5-6 years experience.
Must have more than 03 years of work experience in a Singapore healthcare sector
Must have HSPA Certified Registered Central Service Technical Training (CRCST)

Job Summary
Provide Centre-based Nursing and Nursing Assessment and management.

Job Description
Centre-based nursing & Nursing Assessment/review and Management of day care clients;
Implement nursing interventions as outlined in the care plan and carry out nursing procedures according to the care needs of the client;
Provide nursing services requiring substantial and specialized nursing skills (delegating the basic nursing care to the trained care staff [ Nursing Aides/ Community Care Assoc/Healthcare Asst];
Co-ordinate with other team members and updating them of the changes in the clients condition and needs;
Prepare clinical documentation, monitor outcomes of services and perform escalation of cases if there is need for more acute management of clients;
Provide ongoing support and education and updates to the caregivers, clients, families and their medical practitioners;
Provide supervision to Nursing aides, Community Care Associates and Healthcare assistants to ensure they meet the standard of care according to MOH centre-based guidelines;
Facilitate activities that contribute towards the improvement of the quality of client care and support care integration;
Conduct regular competency assessments of care staff and centre staff not limited to hand hygiene, Personal Protection Equipment, transfer of clients; code blue drills, medication assistance;
Assist centre in submission and review of incident report related to clients care;
Provide monthly updates to Director of Nursing/ Centre Manager/ Nurse Manager regarding centre-based nursing service;
Carry out other responsibilities and duties as assigned from time to time, including coverage of other Staff Nurse in other Senior Care facilities if necessary.

Job Requirement
Qualification:
Recognized qualification in Diploma/Degree in Nursing Experience;
A minimum of 5 years experience in clinical area such as acute or community hospital.
Special Aptitude and knowledge:
Good knowledge of the healthcare environment and service processes is important.
Experience in community care provision is an advantage.
Is a person of integrity, highly motivated, a team leader and able to maintain good interpersonal relationships, in collaboration with various partners in the healthcare system.

Working Location
Central

Working Hours
(5 Days Work Week) / Subject to Centre Managers arrangement
7.30 am  5 pm
8.00 am  5.30 pm
8.30 am  6 pm

