Responsibilities:
 Involve in the care teams assessment of clients in maintenance day care, dementia day care and community rehabilitative programmes;
 Develop and implement care plans for clients and their caregivers with other care team members;
 Perform assessment of the clients physical mobility and falls risk;
 Provide appropriate physiotherapy interventions based on assessment of clients;
 Conduct functional mobility, training, including the prescription and use of appropriate mobility and/or walking aids;
 Plan, implement and evaluate individual and group physical activity and exercise programmes;
 Conduct and/or supervise group therapy and exercises for the clients;
 Conduct education and training for clients caregivers; provides support as required;
 Conduct in-service training or/sessions for care staff and volunteers;
 Maintain documentation of clients progress and outcomes of care provision;
 Recommend new strategies to the Manager (FHGCC);

Qualification:
 Diploma/degree in Physiotherapy
 Obtained full registration with the Allied Health Professional Council in Singapore
 Good written and spoken English
 Ability to converse in Mandarin and major dialects is an advantage (in order to conduct education and training for Mandarin and dialect speaking clients caregivers and provides support as required.)
 A mature individual and a team player with good interpersonal and communication skills
 Possess analytical and problem-solving skills
 Passionate in serving the needy and vulnerable
 Proficient in Microsoft Office  MS Word and Excel

The Services required are set out as follows:
 Assessment and Identification of high-at-risk students  observe and identify key needs of students using relevant tools, discuss needs and intervention plans with relevant school personnel;
 Outreach and engagement - engage and build positive relationships with identified students during and/or outside of curriculum hours, engage and connect with identified students in community settings outside of school compound, and equip students with essential socio-emotional knowledge and skills;
 Case management and Family Engagement  provide case planning, management and counselling support, and conduct family engagement and interventions;
 School collaboration  provide relevant feedback and progress of students to school personnel, and provide support and consultation to school teachers on students needs and challenges.

The Department of Medicine is seeking candidates who are highly motivated and willing to join the Division of Dermatology for a challenging and fulfilling appointment as a Dermatologist Consultant/Associate Consultant.

The Division of Dermatology manages in-patients and out-patients with a wide spectrum of dermatological diseases. As a tertiary centre, the Division of Dermatology provides specialised dermatological services and nurtures various dermatological sub-specialties. The division has a strong culture of research and education.

Job Requirements:
Possess both basic Medical and Post-graduate Degrees which are registerable with the Singapore Medical Council;
Active in clinical practice;
Completed 1 year of housemanship with 3 year of post-housemanship clinical experience;
Must possess the relevant experience in dermatology at a Specialist level upon the completion of specialist training;
Able to work independently with demonstrated competence in managing patients in the department; and
Confident with initiative and a good team player

Interested candidates can send their detailed resume including 2 appointed character referees (name, designation, companys name, email address, contact number) to: medical@nuhs.edu.sg
We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

The National University Health System (NUHS) is an integrated Academic Health System and Regional Health System in Singapore that delivers value-driven, innovative and sustainable healthcare. Institutions in the NUHS group include three hospitals  National University Hospital, Ng Teng Fong General Hospital and Jurong Community Hospital; three National Specialty Centres  National University Cancer Institute, Singapore, National University Heart Centre, Singapore and National University Centre for Oral Health, Singapore; a polyclinic group  the National University Polyclinics; one medical centre  Jurong Medical Centre; and three academic health sciences institutions  National University of Singapore (NUS) Yong Loo Lin School of Medicine (including the Alice Lee Centre for Nursing Studies), NUS Faculty of Dentistry and NUS Saw Swee Hock School of Public Health.

